Prep the ingredients: Chop the @scallions{1}(chopped), keeping the whites and greens
separate. Mince the @garlic{2%cloves}(minced). Drain and rinse the @kidney beans{13.4%ounce}.
Core, seed, and remove the white veins from the @poblano pepper{1}, then dice into
½-inch cubes. Halve, peel and dice the @yellow onion{1}(peeled and diced).

Brown the beef: Heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over
medium–high heat. Add the @ground beef{10%ounce} and cook, breaking up the pieces,
for about ~{5-6%minutes}, or until golden brown and no longer pink. Season with
@salt{} and @pepper{} and set aside.

Cook the vegetables: Add the scallion whites, poblano, onion, and garlic to the pan.
Cook, tossing, for about ~{6%minutes}, or until slightly softened. Add @chili powder{1%tsp}
and @cumin{1%tsp} and cook, stirring, for ~{30%seconds}. Season with salt and pepper.

Simmer the chili: Add the @beef stock concentrate{1}, beans, @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounce},
and 1 cup water to the pan. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a simmer and cook for
about ~{10%minutes}, or until thickened. Season with salt and pepper.

> TIP: If you have time, keep it simmering on the stove for longer! It gets better the
> longer it cooks.

Plate: Serve the chili divided between #bowls{} with a sprinkle of @cheddar cheese{1%ounce},
the scallion greens, and a dollop of @sour cream{2%ounce}!